1. Flight Booking System

A user searches for flights, books a seat, and receives a booking confirmation with PNR. Validate seat availability, passenger data, payment, and inventory update.

Sample request / response JSON

POST /api/v1/bookings
{
  "flightId": "AI-202",
  "passenger": {
    "name": "Priya Sharma",
    "dob": "1992-04-15",
    "passportNo": "N1234567",
    "email": "priya@example.com"
  },
  "seatClass": "economy",
  "seats": 2,
  "payment": {
    "method": "card",
    "amount": 8500.00,
    "currency": "INR"
  }
}
{
  "status": "CONFIRMED",
  "pnr": "PNR7X29K",
  "flightId": "AI-202",
  "totalAmount": 8500.00,
  "seats": ["14A","14B"],
  "boardingTime": "2026-07-01T06:30:00Z",
  "errors": []
}
5 helper functions to implement

checkFlightExists(flightId)
checkSeatAvailability(flightId, seatClass, qty)
validatePassengerDetails(passenger)
processPayment(payment)
generatePNR(flightId, passenger)
Test scenarios to cover

Happy path — 2 economy seats
Sold-out flight → FAILED
Invalid passport format → 400
Payment failure → PAYMENT_FAILED
Duplicate booking same PNR




2.2. Hospital Appointment Booking

