  4. Banking Fund Transfer

  User initiates an IMPS/NEFT transfer. Validate sender balance, beneficiary account, transfer limits, and generate transaction reference.

  Sample request / response JSON

  POST /api/v1/transfers
  {
    "transferType": "IMPS",
    "sender": {
      "accountNo": "9988001122",
      "ifsc": "HDFC0001234",
      "mpin": "****"
    },
    "beneficiary": {
      "accountNo": "1122334455",
      "ifsc": "SBIN0004567",
      "name": "Arun Kumar"
    },
    "amount": 25000.00,
    "currency": "INR",
    "remarks": "Rent July 2026",
    "notifyBeneficiary": true
  }
  {
    "transactionId": "TXN20260609HDFC882211",
    "status": "SUCCESS",
    "transferType": "IMPS",
    "amount": 25000.00,
    "charges": 5.00,
    "netDeducted": 25005.00,
    "timestamp": "2026-06-09T14:22:33+05:30",
    "rrn": "620914528831",
    "senderBalance": 74995.00,
    "errors": []
  }
  5 helper functions to implement

  validateSenderAccount(accountNo, ifsc, mpin)
  checkSufficientBalance(accountNo, amount)
  validateBeneficiary(accountNo, ifsc, name)
  checkTransferLimits(transferType, amount)
  executeTransferAndNotify(sender, beneficiary, amount)
  Test scenarios to cover

  Successful IMPS transfer
  Insufficient balance → INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS
  Invalid beneficiary IFSC → 422
  Daily limit exceeded → LIMIT_EXCEEDED
  Wrong MPIN → AUTH_FAILED
  Bank server down → 503

